Version 1.11:
	Send EV_SYN/SYN_REPORT after every uinput event to force certain things (i.e new X versions) to acknowledge the event before the device is destroyed. Running kbbind with -r disables this.

Version 1.1:
	Added kbbind(1) manpage.
	
	Bugfix: Do not allow "map" with a single argument.
	
	Bugfix: Handle "drop" directive.
	
	Added key alias support.
	
	Bugfix: Exit on SIGTERM without waiting for an event.

Version 1.0:
	Initial Release
